---
import Container from '../components/Container.astro';
import Panel from '../components/Panel.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';

const title = "Privacy Policy - PT Authority Hub";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>{title}</title>
</head>
<body class="bg-bg text-text">
  <Container className="py-24">
    <a href="/" class="text-accent hover:underline mb-8 inline-block">‚Üê Back to home</a>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-12">Privacy Policy</h1>
    
    <Panel className="prose prose-invert max-w-none p-8 sm:p-12">
      <div class="space-y-8 text-muted leading-relaxed sm:text-[18px]">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-text text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Introduction</h2>
          <p>We take your privacy seriously. This policy explains how we collect and use your data when you use the PT Authority Hub landing page and services.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-text text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Collection</h2>
          <p>We collect information you provide through our intake forms and (if opted-in) your uploaded fitness data. This includes your name, email, goals, and metrics like sleep and recovery scores.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-text text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Data Retention</h2>
          <p>We only keep your data for as long as necessary to provide our services. Specifically, raw fitness data is deleted from our systems within 30 days after your audit is delivered.</p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-text text-2xl font-bold mb-4">Your Rights</h2>
          <p>You have the right to request access to your data or its deletion at any time. Simply contact us via our support channels.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </Panel>
  </Container>
</body>
</html>
